acy unknown post-turnover. Not confirmed as champion. Mentioned 'estimated costing,' suggesting involvement in financial review.", "role": "Influencer", "title": "Data Analytics and Financial Performance Manager", "sentiment": "neutral to positive (re-engaged 2 Jul)", "last_contact_date": "2026-07-02"}, {"name": "Christian Pinter", "risk": "Departed HAECO as part of full evaluation team turnover 6 Jun 2026 per Next_Step. Current status unknown; may have left or may be part of new team Carl is attempting to re-engage.", "role": "Unknown", "title": "Group Procurement General Manager", "sentiment": "unknown post-turnover", "last_contact_date": "2026-06-06"}, {"name": "Nicola Or", "risk": "Departed HAECO as part of full evaluation team turnover 6 Jun 2026 per Next_Step. Current status unknown.", "role": "Unknown", "title": "Head Of Procurement", "sentiment": "unknown post-turnover", "last_contact_date": "2026-06-06"}, {"name": "Joey Eley", "risk": "Departed HAECO as part of full evaluation team turnover 6 Jun 2026 per Next_Step. Current status unknown.", "role": "Unknown", "title": "Head of Group Procurement Governance", "sentiment": "unknown post-turnover", "last_contact_date": "2026-06-06"}, {"name": "CHERIS TSANG", "risk": "Departed HAECO as part of full evaluation team turnover 6 Jun 2026 per Next_Step. Current status unknown.", "role": "Unknown", "title": "Procurement Manager", "sentiment": "unknown post-turnover", "last_contact_date": "2026-06-06"}, {"name": "Simon Fung", "risk": "Left HAECO 8 May 2026 per prior record. Was the primary technical evaluator and champion candidate, raised part-number golden-record requirement as 'potential showstopper' (Next_Step 13 Mar 2026). His departure removed the strongest internal advocate and technical relationship.", "role": "Evaluator", "title": "Group IT Business Analysis Manager", "sentiment": "gone (left HAECO)", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-08"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Next_Step 26 Jan 2026: part-number and category-management pain", "Next_Step 2 Jul 2026: Charlotte reference to 'estimated costing'", "Synthesis fields (Customer_Business_Problem__c, Business_Objectives__c, Value_to_Customer__c) not returned by SOQL"], "narrative": "The buyer articulated operational pain around part-number records and category management across 7-8 entities within the Swire Group conglomerate, per Next_Step 26 Jan 2026: 'Main pain points related with Part # records and category management.' Charlotte Lollieron-Bernard mentioned 'estimated costing' in the 2 Jul Next_Step update, suggesting ROI or budget scrutiny is in play. However, no quantified business case has been documented: no cost savings target, headcount reduction, cycle-time improvement, error-rate reduction, or ROI figure from any call, task, or Salesforce field. The Customer_Business_Problem__c, Business_Objectives__c, and Value_to_Customer__c synthesis fields were not returned by SOQL (likely not present in this org or genuinely empty). Without a quantified value case tied to a named buyer stakeholder, the deal lacks the financial anchor required for C-level sign-off on a $450k investment. Quantifying the business case is the immediate gap to close."}, "champion": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["OpportunityContactRole: Simon Fung (Evaluator, prior champion candidate, left 8 May 2026 per prior record)", "Next_Step 6 Jun 2026: 'All of evaluation team has now departed HAECO'", "Next_Step 2 Jul 2026: Charlotte re-appeared in update, current role and advocacy unknown", "Next_Step 2 Jul 2026: Carl attempting to 'set up F2F and navigate execo levels,' awaiting buyer reply", "Synthesis fields (X10b_Champion_Business_Buyer__c, Champion_Identified__c) not returned by SOQL", "No evidence of advocacy or competitive blocking from any current contact"], "narrative": "No active champion exists. Simon Fung (Group IT Business Analysis Manager, Evaluator contact role) was the closest champion candidate through May 2026, driving the technical evaluation and engaging on the part-number golden-record requirement (Next_Step 13 Mar 2026), but Simon left HAECO on 8 May 2026 per prior record. Next_Step 6 Jun 2026 confirmed 'All of evaluation team has now departed HAECO,' meaning Charlotte Lollieron-Bernard, Christian Pinter, Nicola Or, Joey Eley, CHERIS TSANG, and all other prior contacts are also gone. Charlotte re-appeared in the Next_Step 2 Jul 2026 update ('Updated by the relevant stakeholder coming shortly- and looked at estimated costing- deal is back in motion'), suggesting she may have returned or a new Charlotte has joined, but her current role, authority, and willingness to champion Zycus are entirely unknown. No evidence of advocacy (introductions, internal mobilization, competitive blocking) has been observed from Charlotte or any other contact. The X10b_Champion_Business_Buyer__c and Champion_Identified__c synthesis fields were not returned by the relevant stakeholder 2 Jul outreach aims to 'set up F2F and navigate execo levels,' indicating an attempt to rebuild relationships and identify a new champion, but the buyer has not yet responded. Building a champion from scratch with the new team is the foundational move for deal restart."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Salesforce Competitors__c: Coupa, GEP Worldwide, iValua, SAP Ariba", "Next_Step 26 Nov 2025: 'Highly competitive' deal within Swire Group", "Next_Step 18 Mar 2026: Zycus win themes (speed, simplicity, AI execution, industry expertise, ST Eng reference)", "Next_Step 6 Jun 2026: team turnover resets competitive positioning, all vendors return to equal footing", "Synthesis fields (Others_Competitors_Please_specify__c, Why_not_Zycus__c, Zycus_Differentiation_Why_Zycus__c) not returned by SOQL", "Zero Avoma calls discovered to confirm buyer sentiment on competitors"], "narrative": "Four competitors are logged in Salesforce Competitors__c: Coupa, GEP Worldwide, iValua, and SAP Ariba. Next_Step 26 Nov 2025 noted the deal is 'Highly competitive as part of largest HK conglomerate Swire Holding (HK Flagship),' confirming a multi-vendor evaluation from the outset. No Avoma calls were discovered to provide buyer quotes on competitive positioning, and the Others_Competitors_Please_specify__c, How_are_you_addressing_your_problem_toda__c, Existing_vendor__c, Why_not_Zycus__c, and Zycus_Differentiation_Why_Zycus__c synthesis fields were not returned by the relevant stakeholder_Step 18 Mar 2026 listed Zycus win themes as 'speed, simplicity, AI execution, Industry expertise' and referenced 'credentials built around our ST Eng experience,' indicating Zycus is leveraging the Singapore Technologies Engineering (ST Eng) reference as social proof in the aerospace/MRO vertical. However, with the entire evaluation team departed 6 Jun 2026, all four competitors return to equal footing in the restart, and the new team's vendor preferences are unknown. GEP Worldwide is marked as primary competitor per prior record, but this must be re-validated. The wedge to activate: position Merlin Intake and Agentic AI (both in Products) as the next-generation procurement intelligence layer that GEP and Ariba do not offer, anchored to the ST Eng proof point and the part-number golden-record pain. However, the window to activate this wedge is narrow (58 days to close), and Carl must first secure the F2F and map the new team's priorities."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Next_Step 26 Jan 2026: 'Main pain points related with Part # records and category management'", "Next_Step 13 Mar 2026: 'centralized part number requirement' flagged as 'Potential showstopper'", "OpportunityContactRole: Simon Fung (Evaluator, left 8 May 2026 per prior record) was prior pain owner", "Next_Step 2 Jul 2026: Charlotte Lollieron-Bernard re-engaged, potential new pain owner post-turnover", "Synthesis fields (Customer_Business_Problem__c, Pain_points_in_the_current_solution__c) not returned by